Name: molybdenum cofactor deficiency type B
Definition: A molybdenum cofactor deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the MOCS2 gene on chromosome 5q11.
Synonym: molybdenum cofactor deficiency complementation group B

Name: molybdenum cofactor deficiency type A
Definition: A molybdenum cofactor deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the MOCS1 gene on chromosome 6p21.
Synonym: molybdenum cofactor deficiency complementation group A

Name: molybdenum cofactor deficiency type C
Definition: A molybdenum cofactor deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the GPHN gene on chromosome 14q23.
Synonym: molybdenum cofactor deficiency complementation group C
